Title:  Adding Seq and Level fields

Seq:    3

Level:  2

Body:

The Notenik default is to sort your pages by their titles â€” but that's no way to organize a book (unless it's a dictionary or an encyclopedia). 

So we need to add Seq and Level fields to our Collection to allow us to impose a reading structure. 

So, if you haven't done that yet, go ahead and do that now.

The easiest way to add these fields is by using the Collection Settings screen, and simply clicking on the appropriate checkboxes. 

Once you've done this, change your Collection Sort option to Seq + Title.

Now you are creating a book that is structured in the form of an outline.

So go ahead and select the folloing menu option: 

+ Collection -> Outline Tab > Outline with Seq

Now you should see a third tab on the left of the window, labeled Outline. 

This allows you to manipulate your book in the form of an outline. 

This will become more useful as you build your book, adding more content. 
